"v.诘问，困扰 【英】 v. 诘问，困扰(to annoy or harass by interrupting with questions or taunts; bait) 【记】 来自heck(加强语气词 ，表示骂)+le 【例】 heckle the performers with shouts v. 诘问, 困扰(通过问题、嘲笑或反对来使别人尴尬或生气) = badger 【记】heck读: 黑客, le乐: 黑客可以在别人的主页上嘲笑反对别人, 使别人尴尬或生气, 从而自己没事儿偷着 le. 【参】hack(v 乱砍; n 雇佣文人); hackneyed(adj 陈腐的; 常见的) 【记】源自hackle；乱砍，辩论时就是通过诘问乱砍别人；音：黑口，黑嘴，总问一些刁钻问题为难别人；音：还口，对刁钻问题还口 【相关】hackle 梳理, 乱砍 heckle (v.)  early 14c., ""to comb (flax or hemp) with a heckle;"" from heckle (n.) or from related Middle Dutch hekelen. Figurative meaning ""to question severely in a bid to uncover weakness"" is from late 18c. ""Long applied in Scotland to the public questioning of parliamentary candidates"" [OED]. Related: Heckled; heckling.    heckle (n.)  ""flax comb,"" c.1300, hechel, perhaps from an unrecorded Old English *hecel or a cognate Germanic word (such as Middle High German hechel, Middle Dutch hekel), from Proto-Germanic *hakila-, from PIE *keg- ""hook, tooth"" (see hook (n.))."
